The paper deals with partitioning sparse matrices and graphs, which is a common problem in many scientific and graph analytics applications. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories in computer science. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely sub-category as the paper proposes heuristics to solve the problem of symmetric rectilinear partitioning of square matrices. 

cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with partitioning sparse matrices, which is a problem in discrete mathematics. 

cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with tiled execution of sparse matrix and graph analytics kernels, which involves numerical computations. 

cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible sub-category as the paper proposes heuristics to solve a complex problem of symmetric rectilinear partitioning of square matrices. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with graph analytics, which is a common application in machine learning.
